B. Batch vs. Online Learning

Batch learning: trained offline, heavy computation

Online learning: continuously learns from data streams
Useful for rapidly changing environments

C. Instance-Based vs. Model-Based

Instance-based: compares new data to stored examples

Model-based: learns a general model (e.g., linear regression)

Conclusion

Chapter 1 introduces the essential ideas of Machine Learning, explains why ML is needed, highlights real-world applications, and classifies ML systems by their learning type and behavior.
It establishes the conceptual foundation for the rest of the book.
